princeton_ansible.title: Remove machines that do not exists from hosts
Renews certificates for geoserver-staging and catalog
Make deploy_user role run on machines with non-standard user setups

comments.body:
On most boxes, `pulsys` is `1000` and `deploy` is `1001`. These boxes diverge as follows:

- ezproxy-test: unreachable for me
- lib-svn-prod1: `svn` is `1001`, `deploy` does not exist
- ruby-office1: `fkayiwa` is `1001`, `deploy` does not exist
- lib-proc4: `systems` is `1000`, `pulsys` is `1001`; `deploy` exists at `1002`
- vireo-prod1: `vireo` is `1001`, `deploy` does not exist
- vireo-staging1: `vireo` is `1001`, `deploy` does not exist
- lib-postgres3: `systems` is `1000`, `pulsys` is `1001`; `deploy` exists at `1002`
- geoserv1: `systems` is `1000`, `pulsys` is `1001`, `geoserver` is `1002`; `deploy` does not exist
- lib-solr2:  `systems` is `1000`, `pulsys` is `1001`, `solr` is `1002`; `deploy` exists at `1003`
- lib-solr3:  `systems` is `1000`, `pulsys` is `1001`; `deploy` exists at `1002` (and `solr` at `1003`)
- libimages2: unreachable for me
- libruby-dev: unreachable for me

The primary purpose of the `deploy` user is to allow deployment of code updates. Some of these machines don't follow that pattern, so they don't absolutely need a `deploy` user. We definitely want a fix for the boxes that do have (or need) the `deploy` user. We may also want to create a `deployable` group in our Ansible inventory for those boxes, and leave out the ones that don't use/need a `deploy` user.

comments.body: The Firestone RR hours are not displaying correctly right now. Can this be fixed? It seems to have been like this for a few weeks or more.

The following finding aid has a combination of languages from the ASpace drop-down and languages that got imported as notes: https://findingaids.princeton.edu/catalog/C1511 . We have found that though multiple languages will display, maybe PULFAlight does not know what to do with the combo of "language" PLUS "language of materials note" : https://aspace.princeton.edu/staff/resources/4018#tree::resource_4018
On the other hand, this FA with multiple languages displays correctly: https://findingaids.princeton.edu/catalog/C1249 , oh, but now I am seeing that someone put both languages into one string in the language field in ASpace: https://aspace.princeton.edu/staff/resources/4005/edit#tree::resource_4005

Here is one that Will just fixed so that doesn't have those notes on language of materials anymore; but he would love to have the various languages separated by semicolons: https://findingaids.princeton.edu/catalog/MC296
